{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1033,"text":"In 1956, a documentary\nby Jacques Cousteau won"},{"time":5841,"text":"both the Palme d'Or and an Oscar award."},{"time":8866,"text":"This film was called,\n\"Le Monde Du Silence,\""},{"time":11751,"text":"or, \"The Silent World.\""},{"time":14427,"text":"The premise of the title was that\nthe underwater world was a quiet world."},{"time":20459,"text":"We now know, 60 years later,"},{"time":22798,"text":"that the underwater world\nis anything but silent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26677,"text":"Although the sounds\nare inaudible above water"},{"time":29708,"text":"depending on where you are\nand the time of year,"},{"time":33042,"text":"the underwater soundscape can be as noisy\nas any jungle or rainforest."},{"time":39791,"text":"Invertebrates like snapping shrimp,\nfish and marine mammals"},{"time":44673,"text":"all use sound."},{"time":46354,"text":"They use sound to study their habitat,"},{"time":49291,"text":"to keep in communication with each other,"},{"time":51617,"text":"to navigate,"},{"time":52924,"text":"to detect predators and prey."},{"time":55737,"text":"They also use sound by listening\nto know something about their environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61050,"text":"Take, for an example, the Arctic."},{"time":63753,"text":"It's considered a vast,\ninhospitable place,"},{"time":67005,"text":"sometimes described as a desert,"},{"time":69610,"text":"because it is so cold and so remote"},{"time":72567,"text":"and ice-covered for much of the year."},{"time":75268,"text":"And despite this,"},{"time":77005,"text":"there is no place on Earth\nthat I would rather be than the Arctic,"},{"time":81073,"text":"especially as days lengthen\nand spring comes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85464,"text":"To me, the Arctic really\nembodies this disconnect"},{"time":89791,"text":"between what we see on the surface\nand what's going on underwater."},{"time":95685,"text":"You can look out across the ice --\nall white and blue and cold --"},{"time":101691,"text":"and see nothing."},{"time":103653,"text":"But if you could hear underwater,"},{"time":106314,"text":"the sounds you would hear\nwould at first amaze"},{"time":109719,"text":"and then delight you."},{"time":111830,"text":"And while your eyes are seeing\nnothing for kilometers but ice,"},{"time":115876,"text":"your ears are telling you that out there\nare bowhead and beluga whales,"},{"time":121363,"text":"walrus and bearded seals."},{"time":124661,"text":"The ice, too, makes sounds."},{"time":126594,"text":"It screeches and cracks\nand pops and groans,"},{"time":130102,"text":"as it collides and rubs when temperature\nor currents or winds change."},{"time":136112,"text":"And under 100 percent sea ice\nin the dead of winter,"},{"time":140784,"text":"bowhead whales are singing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144247,"text":"And you would never expect that,"},{"time":146138,"text":"because we humans,"},{"time":148353,"text":"we tend to be very visual animals."},{"time":151434,"text":"For most of us, but not all,"},{"time":154503,"text":"our sense of sight is how\nwe navigate our world."},{"time":157725,"text":"For marine mammals that live underwater,"},{"time":160441,"text":"where chemical cues\nand light transmit poorly,"},{"time":164328,"text":"sound is the sense by which they see."},{"time":168427,"text":"And sound transmits very well underwater,"},{"time":170765,"text":"much better than it does in air,"},{"time":172721,"text":"so signals can be heard\nover great distances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176270,"text":"In the Arctic, this\nis especially important,"},{"time":179385,"text":"because not only do Arctic marine\nmammals have to hear each other,"},{"time":183322,"text":"but they also have to listen\nfor cues in the environment"},{"time":186457,"text":"that might indicate\nheavy ice ahead or open water."},{"time":190862,"text":"Remember, although they spend\nmost of their lives underwater,"},{"time":194285,"text":"they are mammals,"},{"time":195533,"text":"and so they have to surface to breathe."},{"time":198458,"text":"So they might listen\nfor thin ice or no ice,"},{"time":202338,"text":"or listen for echoes off nearby ice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207094,"text":"Arctic marine mammals live in a rich\nand varied underwater soundscape."},{"time":212726,"text":"In the spring,"},{"time":213992,"text":"it can be a cacophony of sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217329,"text":"(Marine mammal sounds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233169,"text":"But when the ice is frozen solid,"},{"time":236083,"text":"and there are no big temperature\nshifts or current changes,"},{"time":239815,"text":"the underwater Arctic has some\nof the lowest ambient noise levels"},{"time":244138,"text":"of the world's oceans."},{"time":245882,"text":"But this is changing."},{"time":247228,"text":"This is primarily due to a decrease\nin seasonal sea ice,"},{"time":251796,"text":"which is a direct result of human\ngreenhouse gas emissions."},{"time":256354,"text":"We are, in effect, with climate change,"},{"time":259284,"text":"conducting a completely uncontrolled\nexperiment with our planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263765,"text":"Over the past 30 years,"},{"time":265878,"text":"areas of the Arctic have seen\ndecreases in seasonal sea ice"},{"time":269755,"text":"from anywhere from\nsix weeks to four months."},{"time":274820,"text":"This decrease in sea ice is sometimes\nreferred to as an increase"},{"time":279454,"text":"in the open water season."},{"time":281341,"text":"That is the time of year when\nthe Arctic is navigable to vessels."},{"time":285560,"text":"And not only is the extent\nof ice changing,"},{"time":289345,"text":"but the age and the width of ice is, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293356,"text":"Now, you may well have heard"},{"time":294838,"text":"that a decrease in seasonal sea ice\nis causing a loss of habitat"},{"time":298345,"text":"for animals that rely on sea ice,"},{"time":300500,"text":"such as ice seals,\nor walrus, or polar bears."},{"time":304858,"text":"Decreasing sea ice is also causing\nincreased erosion along coastal villages,"},{"time":309721,"text":"and changing prey availability\nfor marine birds and mammals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314319,"text":"Climate change and decreases in sea ice"},{"time":317421,"text":"are also altering the underwater\nsoundscape of the Arctic."},{"time":323370,"text":"What do I mean by soundscape?"},{"time":325833,"text":"Those of us who eavesdrop\non the oceans for a living"},{"time":328714,"text":"use instruments called hydrophones,"},{"time":330992,"text":"which are underwater microphones,"},{"time":333061,"text":"and we record ambient noise --"},{"time":335031,"text":"the noise all around us."},{"time":336979,"text":"And the soundscape describes\nthe different contributors"},{"time":340344,"text":"to this noise field."},{"time":342743,"text":"What we are hearing on our hydrophones"},{"time":345368,"text":"are the very real sounds\nof climate change."},{"time":349503,"text":"We are hearing these changes\nfrom three fronts:"},{"time":352831,"text":"from the air,"},{"time":354627,"text":"from the water"},{"time":356104,"text":"and from land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358319,"text":"First: air."},{"time":361904,"text":"Wind on water creates waves."},{"time":364541,"text":"These waves make bubbles;"},{"time":366390,"text":"the bubbles break,"},{"time":367781,"text":"and when they do,"},{"time":369311,"text":"they make noise."},{"time":370538,"text":"And this noise is like a hiss\nor a static in the background."},{"time":375298,"text":"In the Arctic, when it's ice-covered,"},{"time":378273,"text":"most of the noise from wind\ndoesn't make it into the water column,"},{"time":381928,"text":"because the ice acts as a buffer\nbetween the atmosphere and the water."},{"time":387000,"text":"This is one of the reasons"},{"time":388369,"text":"that the Arctic can have\nvery low ambient noise levels."},{"time":392834,"text":"But with decreases in seasonal sea ice,"},{"time":395488,"text":"not only is the Arctic now open\nto this wave noise,"},{"time":400459,"text":"but the number of storms\nand the intensity of storms in the Arctic"},{"time":403970,"text":"has been increasing."},{"time":405725,"text":"All of this is raising noise levels\nin a previously quiet ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410748,"text":"Second: water."},{"time":414481,"text":"With less seasonal sea ice,"},{"time":416379,"text":"subarctic species are moving north,"},{"time":419079,"text":"and taking advantage of the new habitat\nthat is created by more open water."},{"time":424504,"text":"Now, Arctic whales, like this bowhead,"},{"time":427553,"text":"they have no dorsal fin,"},{"time":429289,"text":"because they have evolved to live\nand swim in ice-covered waters,"},{"time":434081,"text":"and having something sticking\noff of your back is not very conducive"},{"time":437628,"text":"to migrating through ice,"},{"time":439462,"text":"and may, in fact, be excluding\nanimals from the ice."},{"time":443835,"text":"But now, everywhere we've listened,"},{"time":446506,"text":"we're hearing the sounds\nof fin whales and humpback whales"},{"time":449588,"text":"and killer whales,"},{"time":451081,"text":"further and further north,"},{"time":453336,"text":"and later and later in the season."},{"time":456003,"text":"We are hearing, in essence,"},{"time":457439,"text":"an invasion of the Arctic\nby subarctic species."},{"time":461874,"text":"And we don't know what this means."},{"time":463861,"text":"Will there be competition for food\nbetween Arctic and subarctic animals?"},{"time":468965,"text":"Might these subarctic species introduce\ndiseases or parasites into the Arctic?"},{"time":475035,"text":"And what are the new sounds\nthat they are producing"},{"time":477836,"text":"doing to the soundscape underwater?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":480980,"text":"And third: land."},{"time":483188,"text":"And by land ..."},{"time":484868,"text":"I mean people."},{"time":486714,"text":"More open water means\nincreased human use of the Arctic."},{"time":491254,"text":"Just this past summer,"},{"time":492596,"text":"a massive cruise ship made its way\nthrough the Northwest Passage --"},{"time":496801,"text":"the once-mythical route\nbetween Europe and the Pacific."},{"time":501386,"text":"Decreases in sea ice have allowed\nhumans to occupy the Arctic more often."},{"time":508167,"text":"It has allowed increases in oil\nand gas exploration and extraction,"},{"time":512832,"text":"the potential for commercial shipping,"},{"time":515486,"text":"as well as increased tourism."},{"time":518394,"text":"And we now know that ship noise increases\nlevels of stress hormones in whales"},{"time":523283,"text":"and can disrupt feeding behavior."},{"time":526051,"text":"Air guns, which produce loud,\nlow-frequency \"whoomps\""},{"time":531324,"text":"every 10 to 20 seconds,"},{"time":533922,"text":"changed the swimming and vocal\nbehavior of whales."},{"time":537723,"text":"And all of these sound sources\nare decreasing the acoustic space"},{"time":542685,"text":"over which Arctic marine mammals\ncan communicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546914,"text":"Now, Arctic marine mammals\nare used to very high levels of noise"},{"time":551322,"text":"at certain times of the year."},{"time":553327,"text":"But this is primarily from other\nanimals or from sea ice,"},{"time":557427,"text":"and these are the sounds\nwith which they've evolved,"},{"time":559947,"text":"and these are sounds that are vital\nto their very survival."},{"time":563461,"text":"These new sounds\nare loud and they're alien."},{"time":567161,"text":"They might impact the environment\nin ways that we think we understand,"},{"time":572336,"text":"but also in ways that we don't."},{"time":576998,"text":"Remember, sound is the most\nimportant sense for these animals."},{"time":581823,"text":"And not only is the physical habitat\nof the Arctic changing rapidly,"},{"time":586422,"text":"but the acoustic habitat is, too."},{"time":589086,"text":"It's as if we've plucked these animals up\nfrom the quiet countryside"},{"time":592827,"text":"and dropped them into a big city\nin the middle of rush hour."},{"time":596837,"text":"And they can't escape it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599685,"text":"So what can we do now?"},{"time":603019,"text":"We can't decrease wind speeds"},{"time":605431,"text":"or keep subarctic animals\nfrom migrating north,"},{"time":608635,"text":"but we can work on local solutions"},{"time":611092,"text":"to reducing human-caused underwater noise."},{"time":614817,"text":"One of these solutions\nis to slow down ships"},{"time":617998,"text":"that traverse the Arctic,"},{"time":619812,"text":"because a slower ship is a quieter ship."},{"time":623934,"text":"We can restrict access\nin seasons and regions"},{"time":627750,"text":"that are important for mating\nor feeding or migrating."},{"time":632497,"text":"We can get smarter about quieting ships"},{"time":635825,"text":"and find better ways\nto explore the ocean bottom."},{"time":639727,"text":"And the good news is,"},{"time":641694,"text":"there are people\nworking on this right now."},{"time":646240,"text":"But ultimately,"},{"time":647765,"text":"we humans have to do the hard work"},{"time":650656,"text":"of reversing or at the very\nleast decelerating"},{"time":654836,"text":"human-caused atmospheric changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657332,"text":"So, let's return to this idea\nof a silent world underwater."},{"time":663006,"text":"It's entirely possible"},{"time":664525,"text":"that many of the whales\nswimming in the Arctic today,"},{"time":667886,"text":"especially long-lived species\nlike the bowhead whale"},{"time":671445,"text":"that the Inuits say can live\ntwo human lives --"},{"time":675226,"text":"it's possible that these whales\nwere alive in 1956,"},{"time":679011,"text":"when Jacques Cousteau made his film."},{"time":681877,"text":"And in retrospect,"},{"time":683613,"text":"considering all the noise\nwe are creating in the oceans today,"},{"time":688644,"text":"perhaps it really was \"The Silent World.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":692873,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694161,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}